  "firstAcquaintance": "A ghost with demon horns and a very large chest, suffering from severe amnesia.\nShe once made a name for herself on the demon battlefields.",
  "personality": "Due to her amnesia, her personality has become childlike - easy to get along with but also easy to deceive. She makes many friends, though she quickly forgets them.",
  "like": "Glass bottles, shiny objects",
  "familiarData": "Ulrika was once a rare demon swordswoman known as the \"Void Demon Sword.\" She fought in the war against the Kingdom Alliance and defeated many formidable opponents, but ultimately fell in battle against overwhelming numbers.\nYears later, when the battlefield ruins were being cleared, Ulrika's soul awakened and she became one of the ghost race, possessing the unique ability to telekinetically control swords and armor.\nUpon resurrecting as a ghost, she lost her ability to form memories, only retaining fragments of her past life and short-term memories from the last few days. This troubled the ghost folk who wanted to take her in, and they eventually let her wander freely.\nThe slave merchant Sophia knew of Ulrika's reputation and frequently approached her, as Ulrika in this state could be of use to her. Ulrika often wanders around the slave market, becoming one of its local urban legends.\nThough she is a ghost, she has enough magical power to materialize. Combined with her tendency to forget she is a ghost, she often behaves in very un-ghostlike ways.",
